On this Father's Day, we are honored to celebrate the life of @mikaelashiffrin’s late father Jeff, by announcing that the Jeff Shiffrin Athlete Resiliency Fund will live on as a newly established need-based, direct-to-athlete funding source for U.S. Ski & Snowboard athletes. 

We are deeply grateful to the Shiffrin family—Eileen, Taylor, and Mikaela—for their dedication and support in establishing this ongoing fund, for their commitment to athletes across all sports, and for their desire to honor Jeff’s legacy through this fund. 🤍

Learn more/donate at keeptheflamealive.org. (Link in bio)
#keeptheflamealive
#fathersday

The #TokyoOlympics may be over, but the flame is still burning with #Beijing2022 right around the corner. 🔥 

This past Father’s Day, in collaboration with the Shiffrin family, we announced the relaunch of the Jeff Shiffrin Athlete Resiliency Fund campaign. The focus of the new campaign is to establish need-based, direct-to-athlete funding for the national team athletes. Our goal is to raise $125,000 in donations that will be matched by an anonymous donor for a total of $250,000 in athlete support. Thanks to your incredible support, we’re almost at goal. 🙏

Learn more/donate at keeptheflamealive.org (link in bio). #keeptheflamealive
